{"@context": "http://schema.org", "@type": "Movie", "url": "/title/tt0100054/", "name": "Lord of the Flies", "image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDczN2I3NzItNjdlMS00YmNhLTkyODQtZGI1YWQ0NmViMTgwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjMwMjk0MTQ@._V1_.jpg", "genre": ["Adventure", "Drama", "Thriller"], "contentRating": "R", "actor": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001267/", "name": "Balthazar Getty"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0299077/", "name": "Chris Furrh"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0684999/", "name": "Danuel Pipoly"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0197647/", "name": "James Badge Dale"}], "director": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0393591/", "name": "Harry Hook"}, "creator": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0325717/", "name": "William Golding"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0696319/", "name": "Jay Presson Allen"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0040620/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0035346/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0020346/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0046515/"}], "description": "Lord of the Flies is a movie starring Balthazar Getty, Chris Furrh, and Danuel Pipoly. Stranded on an island, a group of schoolboys degenerate into savagery.", "datePublished": "1990-03-16", "keywords": "conch,savagery,twins,sea,cruelty", "aggregateRating": {"@type": "AggregateRating", "ratingCount": 27971, "bestRating": "10.0", "worstRating": "1.0", "ratingValue": "6.4"}, "review": {"@type": "Review", "itemReviewed": {"@type": "CreativeWork", "url": "/title/tt0100054/"}, "author": {"@type": "Person", "name": "claudio_carvalho"}, "dateCreated": "2007-03-30", "inLanguage": "English", "name": "A Society Without Perspectives and Rules", "reviewBody": "After a plane crash in the ocean, a group of military students reach an island. The boy Ralph (Balthazar Getty) organizes the other kids, assigning responsibilities for each one. When the rebel Jack Merridew (Chris Furrh) neglects the fire camp and they lose the chance to be seen by a helicopter, the group split under the leadership of Jack. While Ralph rationalizes the survival procedures, Jack returns to the primitivism, using the fear for the unknown (in a metaphor to the religion) and hunger to control the other boys. His group starts hunting and chasing pigs, stealing the possession of Ralph's group and even killing people.\n\nI found this impressive movie very scary, since it shows the behavior of children (and human beings) fighting to survive in a society without perspective and rules. My immediate association was with my and other Third World countries, where many children are abandoned by the Government in their poor communities, and without education, perspectives in life and laws, become very young criminals working in gangs of drug dealers and thieves. In this movie, it is exposed how primitive a kid can be without the authority and respect, and this sort of violence is in the headlines of our newspapers almost every day. There are many discussions presently in Brazil about juvenile criminality. I have never the chance of reading this visionary novel; therefore I can not comment is it is a good or a bad adaptation, but I found this movie a frightening study of characters and sociology. My vote is eight.\n\nTitle (Brazil): \"O Senhor das Moscas\" (\"The Lord of the Flies\")", "reviewRating": {"@type": "Rating", "worstRating": "1", "bestRating": "10", "ratingValue": "8"}}, "duration": "PT1H30M", "trailer": {"@type": "VideoObject", "name": "Official Trailer", "embedUrl": "/video/imdb/vi1045872153", "thumbnail": {"@type": "ImageObject", "contentUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZGE5NmNlNzQtNjkyYy00NjhlLWIxOTItZTg0ZWI2MjlhODM2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXRyYW5zY29kZS13b3JrZmxvdw@@._V1_.jpg"}, "thumbnailUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZGE5NmNlNzQtNjkyYy00NjhlLWIxOTItZTg0ZWI2MjlhODM2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXRyYW5zY29kZS13b3JrZmxvdw@@._V1_.jpg", "uploadDate": "2020-08-12T09:24:10Z"}, "c